task.summary: Created dynamic version of resources page, used custom post type to define Resources type and then used custom fields to be used within that type. Used loops to pull data dynamically.
Created Blog page in WP, then selected the created page as default blog page under settings, imported static blog code snippets and converted to dynamic WP page template.
Began editing blog post meta data section, not yet finished, pushing to repo to preserve edits.
Added blog post excerpt dynamic hookups via PHP and fixed a few layout bugs
Additional changes - removed post excerpt footer, removed div tags from excerpt, moved edit post to same line, attempted again to resize excerpt thumbnail
Changes made to adjust template and styling to make it more like the lesson, odd behaviors from heading image and text shifting on scroll.
Modified archive pages template so that it reflects the remainder of the theme.
Fixed multiple bugs that prevented users from seeing full blog posts, fixed classes and layout in some templates.

Added contact page and created fullwidth contact page template, cut from static contact page from earlier lessons to grab everything within the main content section with corresponding divs and then made it dynamic.

Added Contact Form 7, created contact page template from static site, imported HTML code and added Contact Form 7 syntax to hook it up via shortcodes once done. Removed comments in HTML as CF7 was interpreting as
tags.
Demonstration of adding a registered, additional widget to functions.php in order to use the dynamic sidebar function by ID to inject a sidebar onto any page.
Added new custom, registered menu to the footer section to replace bootstrap standard menu, customized and installed.
